# Vybridge Global Footer

Every Vybridge HTML page MUST use the shared footer component. Do not duplicate footer markup in page files.

## Required markup (before `</body>`)

```html
<footer id="vybridge-footer"></footer>
<script src="PATH/assets/footer-templates.js"></script>
<script src="PATH/assets/footer.js"></script>
```

## Script path by page location

| Location | Script paths |
|----------|----------------|
| Root (`index.html`, `how-it-works.html`) | `assets/footer-templates.js`, `assets/footer.js` |
| `uk/` | `../assets/footer-templates.js`, `../assets/footer.js` |
| `public/` | `../assets/footer-templates.js`, `../assets/footer.js` |

## Source files (edit only these for footer changes)

- `components/footer.en.html` — English footer HTML (source of truth)
- `components/footer.uk.html` — Ukrainian footer HTML (source of truth)
- `assets/footer-templates.js` — embedded templates (sync after editing components)
- `assets/footer.css` — footer styles (design system)
- `assets/footer.js` — loader, locale detection, link resolution

After editing `components/footer.*.html`, run `node scripts/sync-footer-templates.js`.

## Language

Footer language is auto-detected from:
1. `data-lang` on `#vybridge-footer` (optional override)
2. `<html lang="uk">` or `/uk/` in the URL path

## New pages checklist

1. Add `<footer id="vybridge-footer"></footer>` after `</main>`
2. Include `footer-templates.js` then `footer.js` with the correct relative paths
3. Do NOT copy footer HTML or CSS into the page file
4. Duplicate EN + UA pages when adding new sections (project convention)
